transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, I can help you today.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'd like to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can take a look into your account.

Speaker 2: What's your last name and your zip code?

Speaker 1: Jim Koenig, K-O-E-N-I-G.

Speaker 2: Okay, I pulled you up here.

Speaker 1: Do you want to mention you have an order that shipped out to you and the team?

Speaker 2: From the trip, you received it yet, but it could be still on its way?

Speaker 1: But I can make an adjustment to any future orders.

Speaker 2: I do want to mention, if I were to cancel all your orders entirely,

Speaker 1: the doctor would also delete the visit from his system and

Speaker 2: you wouldn't be able to order these.

Speaker 1: However, I could always just put you on a six month freeze plan,

Speaker 2: where you can actually call us to get the order sooner or delay them further.

Speaker 1: But this way you can retain access to the medication for

Speaker 2: when you need it down the road.

Speaker 1: No, I'm just going to cancel it.

Speaker 2: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 1: Just keep in mind, sir, moving forward,

Speaker 2: you wouldn't have access to these pills anymore, but you're all set here today.

Speaker 1: Okay, that sounds great.

Speaker 2: All right, I hope you have a good one.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.
